For this release of AOL4Free, I have included my first working hell function. It's probably very primitive compared to what you expected me to write, but I haven't had the time to get down and write a full-fledged assembly based Hell program. However, this will be the fastest mailbomber you will have ever seen. You know how when you send mail (and have the 'Close mail after send' pref turned off) it dims the 'Send Now' button, preventing you from just hitting the enter key over and over again? Well, I hacked AOL's Mail Tool so it doesn't do that anymore.So how does it work? It's a KeyQuencer macro. To invoke it just type cmd-opt-ctrl 'm', and make sure the 'Close mail after send' pref is turned off. Also, you will find under the 'Hell' menu a selection 'Enable Ultrabomb'. When this item is checked, mailbombing will go somewhat faster because AOL4Free's free tokens are not being sent with the mail tokens. The downside, of course, is that you will be charged for the time spent mailbombing. (Aww, poor baby. :)INSTALLATION:First you must import the 'UltraBomb Macro' into your KeyQuencer control panel. Open KeyQuencer and choose 'Import Macros...' from the KeyQuencer File menu. Choose the 'UltraBomb Macro' that's in this folder and it will be put into your list of macros.If you want to customize the macro, just open it up and edit it. It's pretty much self-explanatory.Now all you gotta do is log on AOL4Free and you can mailbomb to your heart's content. You can even watch the chat occuring in a chat room by moving the mail window down below the chat window as the macro is occuring. (You can't participate in the chat, though).With UltraBombing enabled, you should experience a send rate of a little more than one piece of mail per second, which means you can fill someone's box within 8 minutes.Well, I hope you like this little taste of Hell. Just wait until my standalone hell app is released, in a couple months (maybe).Happy